<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2100GMT, Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Hundreds of Israeli troops left south Lebanon under
the cover of darkness early Tuesday morning amid reports that
Israel will end its 22-year occupation of south Lebanon within
days.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in Lebanon said the predawn withdrawal involved
some three-quarters of the Israeli forces in the security zone in
south Lebanon, which Israel set up in 1985 with a self-claimed
purpose of protecting its northern security.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Defense Force (IDF) cleared the Bint Jubeil outpost,
the second largest outpost in the zone, and around 120 IDF officers
and soldiers have withdrawn to Israel overnight, an army statement
said. (Israel-Lebanon)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said on Tuesday
that Israel would complete its accelerated troop withdrawal from
south Lebanon within a few days.
</P>
<P>
"We will redeploy in the next few days on the international
border," Barak told the army radio, hours after his security
cabinet empowered him to speed up the pullout from Israel's
occupation zone in south Lebanon. (Israel-Barak-Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Three quarters of the Israeli occupation troops have
withdrawn from south Lebanon and the remaining quarter is expected
to leave within this week, Voice of Lebanon radio reported Tuesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The larger part of south Lebanon has been freed, including the
border towns of Bint Jebeil and Sweida, both of which were vacated
by Israeli troops overnight, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The main Israeli concentrations are now in the Beaufort Castle
and the town of Marjeyoun in the eastern sector of south Lebanon.
(Lebanon-Israeli Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA) released 144
Lebanese detainees from the notorious Khiam prison Tuesday
afternoon, Oriental radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The detainees, including five women, held uprising in the prison
on Monday when SLA collapsed after Israel began its full scale,
unexpectedly swift withdrawal from the occupied zone this week.
</P>
<P>
The prison, run by the militia in cooperation with Israeli
occupation troops, has been repeatedly accused of human rights
violations including torture. (Lebanon-Khiam Prison)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's withdrawal from south Lebanon early
Tuesday sparked mixed reactions in the country with the government
defending its decision and the opposition accusing it of stirring
up chaos inside the security zone.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Ehud Barak said earlier Tuesday the withdrawal
from south Lebanon is a right decision that the government has
made.
</P>
<P>
The government did the right thing in deciding to bring the
Israeli troops back from south Lebanon, Barak said, adding that by
implementing the United Nations Security Council Resolution 425,
Israel will receive extensive international backing. (Israel-
Pullout-Reactions) 
</P>
</TEXT>
