<HEADLINE> Egypt Hails Israeli Pullout From Lebanon as Victory of Lebanese People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on
Wednesday hailed the Israeli troop pullout from southern Lebanon as
a victory of the Lebanese people.
</P>
<P>
In congratulatory cables sent to Lebanese leaders, Mubarak
termed the end of Israel's occupation of south Lebanon as "a great
victory" for the Lebanese people.
</P>
<P>
It was also "a great achievement" of the international
legitimacy and "a great step for the realization of a just and
comprehensive peace in the Middle East" under the United Nations
Security Council resolutions 425 and 426 and the land-for-peace
principle, he added.
</P>
<P>
Israel invaded Lebanon in 1978 and carved up a border strip as a
so-called "security zone" in 1985 to allegedly protect its northern
area from cross-border attacks by Lebanese Muslim guerrillas. The
U.N. Security Council adopted the two resolutions after the Israeli
invasion, demanding immediate and unconditional Israeli withdrawal
from Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish state decided earlier this year that it would pull
out from Lebanon by July 7. However, it completed withdrawal of
troops from south Lebanon at early hours on Wednesday, ending its
22-year occupation of the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
