<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Prime Minister Meets With Vietnamese Communist Party Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 24 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
met Wednesday with Vietnamese Communist Party General Secretary Le
Kha Phieu, who is on a four-day official visit here since Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jospin briefed Phieu on France's vision of globalization during
the meeting, while Phieu expressed to the prime minister Vietnam's
intention to open up and build relations of partnership with
Europe, in particular with France, according to Agence France-
Presse.
</P>
<P>
Phieu also had a meeting Wednesday with National Assembly
President Raymond Forni.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader will end his visit to France Thursday
with a tour of the European aeronautics producer Airbus consortium,
the French National Center of Space Studies and the City of Space
in Toulouse, southwestern France.
</P>
<P>
Phieu, who is the first Vietnamese Communist Party leader to
visit France, had a meeting with French President Jacques Chirac
Monday and traveled Tuesday on a TGV, or train of great speed, to
the Futuroscope cinema park in Poitiers, central France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
