<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's ruling party Wednesday
dismissed as wild allegation a criticism by a U.S.-based
organization describing the election environment in the southern
African country unfavorable.
</P>
<P>
The National Chairman of the Zimbabwe African National
Union-Patriotic Front (Zanu-pf) John Nkomo said the report
released last week by the U.S.- based National Democratic
Institute for International Affairs (NDI) was geared to smear the
