<HEADLINE> Over 20 Killed, 10 Wounded in Chechnya: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 rebels and at least one
Russian serviceman were killed with another ten federal solders
wounded Wednesday in Russia's breakaway republic of Chechnya,
according to the Russian military.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 militants were killed and their six motor vehicles were
destroyed in the Sharoi-Argun Gorge in southern Chechnya during a
special operation by the Russian forces at around 2 p.m. (1100 GMT)
Wednesday, said Col.Gen. Gennady Troshev, commander of the Russian
forces in the North Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
A federal reconnaissance group spotted a convoy of 13 trucks of
Chechen rebels advancing toward the gorge on an alpine road from
the west to the east, and launched an attack on the convoy. Twenty-
plus rebels were killed, and a truck and five cars were destroyed,
Troshev said.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, a federal paratrooper was killed and another
10 were wounded when their army vehicle belonging to the 104th
airborne regiment struck a landmine near the town of Engenoi in
Chechnya, said the Russian forces' headquarters in the North
Caucasus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
