before gathering facts," he said.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Zimbabwe and Britain were at their lowest ebb
because of the controversial land redistribution program in
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
President Robert Mugabe has said despite international
criticisms of the program, his government would go ahead and
compulsorily acquire land from the country's 4,500 white-owned
commercial farmers to resettle landless Zimbabweans.
</P>
<P>
The white farmers own 70 percent of fertile land in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Britain has warned Mugabe to carry out the program fairly or
else risk losing critical foreign aid. 
