<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High Commission
for Refugees (UNHCR) will send a delegation on Friday to Angola to
assess the humanitarian situation there, said a report reaching
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted UNHCR spokesman Kris Janowski as saying on
Wednesday that the UNHCR was deeply concerned over the worsening
humanitarian situation of war victims and war-displaced people in
northern region of Angola.
</P>
<P>
The 12-member UNHCR delegation will spend two months in the
northern provinces of the country, including Uige and Zaire, said
the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
In the war-torn southwest African country, over two million
people are in need of urgent food aid, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
A UN report published in April said that Angola currently has
3.7 million war-displaced people, facing malnutrition and medicine
shortage. 
