<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensex Down on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
dropped slightly on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) Wednesday as a
late selling spree cut short an attempted brief rally in share
value.
</P>
<P>
The BSE 30-share Sensitive Index opened sharply down at 3,872.7
from Tuesday's close of 3,943.54 and declined to an intra-day low
of 3,840.11. However, emergence of buying in traditional companies
from domestic institutions later pushed up the Sensex to the day's
high of 3,981.46, before ending at 3,933.65, netting a moderate
loss of 9.89 points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index eased by 2.19 points to 1,943.69.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted at 422.09 and 159.
42, little changed from Tuesday's close of 422.6 and 159.98
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index, however, edged up by 0.57 points to 1,281.61.
</P>
</TEXT>
