<HEADLINE> Indian Southern Air Command on Full Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Southern Air Command of the
Indian Air Force (IAF) is in full alert and preparedness to meet
any eventuality arising out of the Sri Lankan crisis, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) quoted IAF sources as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources were quoted as saying preparations were in full
swing as Sri Lanka was barely 30 minutes by air from
Thiruvananthapuram, a major IAF air-base in South India's Kerala
State.
</P>
<P>
The Indian government announced Tuesday that it was ready to
help evacuate an estimated 30,000 Sri Lankan troops trapped in
Jaffna peninsula provided there was a formal request from the Sri
Lankan government under some "proper conditions."
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan government troops have been fighting rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam, who launched attacks to take
back Jaffna, their former stronghold.
</P>
<P>
A PTI report Tuesday said ships of India's Eastern Naval
Command and transport planes of the IAF would be involved in any
possible evacuation missions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Indian Navy and Air Force Wednesday continued
their joint surveillance of the coastal areas of two southern
states, Tamil Nadu and Kerala, the PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
Indian Air Chief Marshal A. Y. Tipnis also arrived in
Thiruvananthapuram Wednesday to inaugurate a three-day conference
of station commanders under the Southern Air Command.
</P>
<P>
Although the air chief's visit was claimed to be "long planned
and scheduled" and have nothing to do with the Sri Lankan crisis,
it assumed significance against the backdrop of the current
situation in Sri Lanka, the PTI asserted.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the conference, Tipnis asked
the staff of the Southern Air Command to be on full alert to face
any eventuality and threat.
</P>
<P>
The general expressed concern over the increasing threat of
terrorism and stressed the vital role of the air force in meeting
various security challenges, the PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
He also assured total support for all projects initiated by the
Southern Air Command to upgrade infrastructure facilities to meet
operational challenges, the PTI added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
