<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Says His Recommendations on Lebanon Stand on Their Own </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 24 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said Wednesday that his recommendations on reinforcing U.N.
forces in southern Lebanon stand on their own and the work the
United Nations did with the parties concerned in the Middle East
prior to Israeli withdrawal from southern Lebanon is still useful
for what is happening in the region.
</P>
<P>
Annan was responding to the conclusion of Israeli withdrawal
from southern Lebanon. According to reports reaching here, the
last of Israel's soldiers in southern Lebanon returned to home
Wednesday, ending a military occupation that spanned 22 years.
</P>
<P>
"For example, the Israeli withdrawal will be to the line that
we have indicated, so that in itself will be useful," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to work with the Lebanese Government in assuring
their own control over the territory and maintain peace in that
part of the region," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"Of course, the law and order functions belong to the
Government of Lebanon, not to us," the U.N. chief said.
</P>
<P>
"So it is quite possible that we will still put in additional
peacekeepers to calm the situation for a while, once we have the
assurances that I've asked for from all the parties," he said.
</P>
<P>
"And then, of course, once the situation is settled and
Lebanon has assumed its full territorial responsibility, the
peacekeepers will withdraw, our work would have been done," Annan
said.
</P>
<P>
"I'm in touch with the troop contributors about deploying. We
still first have to certify the withdrawal of Israeli troops to
the international border, or the line as determined by us, and
then work with the member states to get the reinforcements in,"
Annan added.
</P>
<P>
Annan submitted a report to the Security Council Monday,
recommending that the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (
UNIFIL) be reinforced in order to carry out its responsibilities
under Resolution 425 of 1978.
</P>
<P>
Annan said the total troop strength for carrying out the tasks
related to confirming the withdrawal of Israeli troops would thus
increase from the present Level of 4,513 to approximately 5,600.
</P>
<P>
Once the Israeli withdrawal is confirmed and if the security
situation permits, the force of the UNIFIL would have to be
immediately increased to 7,935 personnel.
</P>
<P>
The report also contains the minimum conditions and
requirements which must be met if Resolution 425 is to be
implemented fully and without conditions and if the United Nations
is to be in a position to fulfill its responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
Israel informed the United Nations in April that it would
complete withdrawal of all its troops from southern Lebanon by
July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
