<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua)-- Following are the highlights of
today's diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 CPC Delegation Leaves for Middle East
</P>
<P>
A friendship delegation of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
headed by Su Rong, an alternate member of the CPC Central
Committee and deputy secretary of the CPC Jilin provincial
committee, left Beijing today for a visit to Iraq and Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is paying the visit at the invitation of the
Arab Baath Socialist party of Iraq and the Working People's
Progressive Party of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
 PLA Chief of General Staff Meets Pakistani Guests
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou, chief of General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), met here today with Abdul Aziz Mirza, chief
of the naval staff of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Fu said that recently the new leader in
Taiwan adopted an evasive and vague attitude towards the one China
principle which serves as the premise and foundation in
settlement of the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the PLA will not sit around idly at any attempts
to split Chinese sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
 CPPCC Chairman Backs Home After Four-Nation Trip
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), returned here
this afternoon after a successful official goodwill visit to
Canada, the Republic Bolivariana of Venezuela, the Republic of
Trinidad and Tobago, and the Republic of Peru.
