<HEADLINE> Shanghai Promotes Logistics Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China's first full-service
logistics corporation, the China Merchants-PSA Logistics Network,
opened here today, a joint-venture financed by China Merchants
Holding and PSA Co. Ltd from Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between PSA, the world's largest container
handler, and China's oldest shipping company aims to provide
comprehensive logistics services for transnational enterprises
doing business in China.
</P>
<P>
China's fledgling logistics industry integrates the flow of
goods, information and capital with the timely, inexpensive
transportation, storage, packing, loading, processing and
distribution of goods.
</P>
<P>
The China Merchants-PSA Logistics Network will offer logistics
services nationwide. It has opened more than 100 routes, mainly in
north, south and central China. 
</P>
