<HEADLINE> Netherlands to Aid Nature Reserve at Mt.Qomolangma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Netherlands' ambassador to China Aer
Ooster said here today that his government has approved 2.5
million US dollars in funding for a nature reserve project at Mt.
Qomolangma.
</P>
<P>
The project proposal was submitted to the Netherlands'
government four years ago by an American institute which
researches mountain ecology. The plan is to help local people
protect the environment and raise their living standard.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, a group of experts in resource management
and forestry will be trained for work in the reserve, and a public
awareness campaign on environmental protection will be launched.
In addition, local enterprises will get financial and technical
support for their development.
</P>
<P>
The national nature reserve at Mt. Qomolangma covers an area of
more than 33,000 square kilometers on the north slope of the
Himalayas. Of the 82,000 residents in the region, over 95 percent
are Tibetan.
</P>
<P>
After years of continuous protection work in the reserve, the
area has seen increased natural vegetation and a rise in wild
animal populations.
</P>
<P>
So far, six international organizations and countries have
joined the project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
