<DOCNO> XIE20000524.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Launches Global Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
launched Wednesday a 1-billion-U.S dollar global bond issue, the
first of ADB's global bond issue this year.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement released here, the ADB said the bonds were
issued with a coupon rate of 7.5 percent per annum payable semi-
annually and with a five-year straight maturity.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based multilateral financial body said the proceeds
of the issue will be part of the ADB's ordinary capital resources
and used in its ordinary (non-concessional) lending operation.
</P>
<P>
The ADB launched two U.S. dollar global bonds in 1999, a 1-
billion-dollar three-year issue and a 1.25-billion-dollar five-
year issue.
</P>
<P>
It also noted that this most recent issue will further develop
ADB's yield curve in U.S. dollar global bonds and further enhance
secondary market liquidity.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1966 to promote economic growth in the Asia and
Pacific region, the ADB has 58 members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
