<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Sets UP New Facility for Crisis Intervention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May (Xinhua) -- A new facility for crisis intervention
has been established by Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaratunga
within the Presidential Secretariat, an official news release said
Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The mission of this special facility is to coordinate
psychological support systems for service personnel and their
dependents during acute crisis situations, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Specific tasks include providing psycho-social support to
service personnel for coping with disability and dysfunction,
giving emotional assistance to dependents in grief, offering
assistance to dependents in tracing those who are injured, missing
and killed in action, and facilitating administrative procedures
related to those killed,injured and missing in action.
</P>
<P>
This facility will also use the service of volunteers who are
already trained by various experts in this subject, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a special committee consisting of parliamentarians
is working at the level of each electorate and attending to the
problems related to service personnel, the release said, adding
that this committee is operating from the Presidential Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan government troops are fighting in the north of the
country with the Tamil rebels, who are fighting for a separate
Tamil state in the island and recently launched fierce attacks on
the troops in a bid to recapture their former stronghold in the
Jaffna Peninsula which they lost in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
