<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Breakthrough in Comprehensive Development of Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China's strategy of developing
agriculture in a comprehensive way has proved successful, with the
pilot zones of the project recording far higher development than
other areas, according to officials and experts attending an on-
going national conference on the matter here today.
</P>
<P>
China launched the project to boost agricultural development
in 1988, when the country was facing a serious shortage of
farmland and water resources, and its middle- and low-yield land
accounted for two-thirds of the country's total. Meanwhile, the
country had a weak agricultural infrastructure and no means of
popularizing agro-technology.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 12 years, China has spent huge sums on the
project, which focused on improving the middle- and low-yield
farmland, spreading information on agricultural technology, and
building up the agricultural infrastructure, and established pilot
zones in more than 1,500 counties nationwide.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999, 20 million hectares of farmland had been
improved and 28 million hectares of improved irrigated land added,
which increased grain production capacity by more than 53 million
tons a year. Added to that, farmers in the pilot zones saw their
annual net income grow by 260 yuan, a significant rise over
earnings in other areas.
</P>
<P>
Funding for the project has come mainly from the central and
local governments, who have divided their investment equally,
along with some bank loans and overseas contributions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000524.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Goals for Comprehensive Development of Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China's comprehensive agricultural
development must now focus on improving the efficiency of
agriculture and raising farmers' income, Minister of Finance Xiang
Huaicheng said here today.
</P>
<P>
The tasks for the current growth stage include continuing to
improve agricultural infrastructure, supporting agriculture
restructuring, promoting agro-technology and ecology, Xiang said
at a National Work Conference on Agricultural Comprehensive
Development.
</P>
<P>
China has been successful with its wide-ranging agro-
development project launched in 1988. Statistics show that the
pilot zones of the project, involving some 1,500 counties, have
increased grain production capacity by over 53 million tons
annually, with their farmers' annual income 260 yuan higher than
in other areas.
</P>
<P>
Xiang said that agricultural production should be market-
oriented, and efforts should be made to develop quality and high-
efficient agriculture by relying on agro-technology.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of environmental protection, saying
that it is closely related to the sustained development of
agriculture. He asked all pilot zones to protect natural forests
and wetlands, and improve farmland ecological protection systems.
</P>
</TEXT>
