<HEADLINE> Shanghai Offers More Investment Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors will find more
opportunities for their cash in Shanghai's industry expansion, and
the upgrading and restructuring of State-owned enterprises, a
senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Shangzhou, executive deputy director of the economic
commission of Shanghai, told a press conference here that the city
's fixed capital industrial investment will reach a total of 62
billion yuan (about 7.5 billion U.S. dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the fixed capital industrial investment in
the country's largest industrial and commercial hub will hit 400
billion yuan in the next five years, which is about the same
amount invested since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The new investment will be put mainly into high-tech industries,
including integrated circuits, fiber and mobile telecommunications
and Internet products, and industries such as jewelry, interior
decoration and cosmetics.
</P>
<P>
Technological progress will account for 55 percent of Shanghai'
s economic growth by the year of 2002, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shanghai will also offer new incentives for foreign
investment in the restructuring of the State-owned enterprises,
the official noted.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four months, Shanghai has approved a total of 323
industrial projects involving foreign funding of 961 million U.S.
dollars, up 58 percent over the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
