<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Says to Hit Syrian Targets in Lebanon if Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Metulla, Israel, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the General Staff
of the Israel Defense Force (IDF) warned Wednesday that Israel will
strike Syrian targets in Lebanon if northern Israel comes under
attack following its troop withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
If there is an attempt to hit the northern residents or Israeli
soldiers we will hit all the power-holding elements in Lebanon
including Syrian targets in Lebanon," Shaul Mofaz told a news
conference at this border city.
</P>
<P>
"The pilots are in a heightened state of readiness and their
quality is known," Mofaz added.
</P>
<P>
This was the most direct warning to date that Israel would hold
Syria, the main power broker in Lebanon, responsible for any
attacks on its northern territory from Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military officially announced earlier that it had
completed troops withdrawal from south Lebanon, ending 22 years of
its presence there.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops poured out of south Lebanon into Israel under the
cover of darkness on Wednesday, as ordered by Prime Minister Ehud
Barak. Tanks and armoured personnel carriers loaded with soldiers
entered Israel through various border crossings.
</P>
<P>
The military said all of the outposts belonging to the Israeli
army and its South Lebanon Army (SLA) allies in the security zone
had been abandoned and most were blown up.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the pullout operations, the sound of heavy shelling
could be heard, the sky was lit by by flares Israeli aircraft
launched to show the way out. But no one was hurt, the military
said.
</P>
<P>
Barak has sent a letter to the United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan, accusing Syria of doing all it could to sabotage the
withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
"To this end, it has been preparing the ground for violent acts
against Israel" after its withdrawal was completed, Barak said in
the letter, urging the United Nations to send peacekeeping forces
into south Lebanon as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
While the withdrawal was going on, thousands of SLA and their
family members sought refugee in Israel and nearly 4,000 of them
have already entered Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel deployed in south Lebanon from 1978 with the self-
declared purpose of halting cross-border attacks and set up the
security zone in 1985 for the same purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
