<HEADLINE> Airports' Operation Management to Be Privatized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
considering privatizing some portions of the operation management
aspect of the country's airports to ensure services of
international standards,Works and Civil Aviation and Tourism
Minister Mosharaff Hossain said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Operation management like cargo handling, ground handling and
duty-free shops of airports would be handed over to the private
sector for enhancing efficiency," the minister said at a function
to mark the inauguration of a 40-seater AN-24 aircraft of Air
Parabat Limited in Sylhet district, some 280 kilometers northeast
of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Hossain said operation management of Sylhet and Chittagong
airports would be privatized in the first phase. A proposal in
this regard would be submitted to the cabinet soon for approval,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the structure of civil aviation would also be
reformed soon. The regulatory side of Civil Aviation Authority
would be under government control while the operation management
side of the airports would be transferred to the private sector,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
