<HEADLINE> South Korea's Trade Surplus Rises in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seoul, May 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's trade surplus reached
247 million U.S. dollars based on customs clearance in April,
bringing the total trade surplus in the first four months of this
year to 765 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In April, the nation's export rose 18.2 percent to 13.59
billion dollars while its import soared 46.6 percent to 13.34
billion dollars compared with the same month of 1999, said the
South Korean Commerce, Industry and Energy Ministry on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Major export items performed very well, with automobiles rising
by 30.2 percent, computers by 79.5 percent, steel by 23.1 percent
and home appliances by 16.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, import in April hit a record high in the country's
history, with the average daily import standing at 620.7 million
dollars. 
</P>
