<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Sweeps South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A heat wave has swept South Korea in
the past two days, with most areas across the nation seeing
temperatures reaching 30 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
North Kyongsang Province registered 34.9 degrees Celsius
Wednesday, said the Korea Meteorological Administration.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, The temperature in Taegu, Pohang, Kumi and Andong
reached 32 degrees Celsius while that of Seoul hit 27 degrees
Celsius. It is 4-9 degrees Celsius higher than average.
</P>
<P>
A heat wave, which usually hits the country in July, but this
year it came much earlier than before and is expected to last
until Friday, said the administration. 
</P>
