<HEADLINE> Most South Korean IT Ventures Based in Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Nealry 80 percent of South Korea's
information technology venture companies are based in Seoul, said
a recent survey conducted by Itis.com Company.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, of 3,525 venture companies registered
on the Web site (www.itiscom.co.kr), 79.2 percent are located in
Seoul and the rest are mainly in Pusan.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 79.2 percent, 32.3 percent are situated along the
Teheran road in Kangnam-gu of Seoul, which is called "Silicon
Valley of South Korea."
</P>
<P>
The IT companies with capital of more than one billion won (
about 880,000 U.S. dollars) account for about 17 percent of the
total.
</P>
<P>
The average number of employees of Seoul-based IT ventures
stands at 10, while the average capital of such companies reaches
100 million won (88,800 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Some 59 percent of Seoul's IT venture firms said they are
involved in business in two or more fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
