<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian container cargo ship was
released today by the Ningbo Maritime Court in East China's
Zhejiang Province after a one-month detainment for severely
damaging a Chinese fishing boat in early April.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian ship, the W/Vabuja, left Ningbo today after paying
135,000 U.S. dollars as compensation for the Chinese fishing boat
and the victims of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian ship is said to have collided with a Chinese
fishing boat on April 2 in the East China Sea near Zhoushan,
causing heavy damage to the Chinese boat, and injuring 13
fishermen.
</P>
<P>
Five of the fishermen were seriously injured, according to
sources with the Ningbo Maritime Court.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xiaopei and five other fishermen, the owners of the ship,
filed a lawsuit with the Ningbo Maritime Court on April 23 for
compensation of 2.38 million yuan (286,700 US dollars), and the
court handed down its decision to detain the ship on the same day.
</P>
