<HEADLINE> HK Awards Quality Taxi Drivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Ten Hong Kong taxi drivers were
awarded the title of "Outstanding Quality Taxi Drivers" and other
20 awarded the title of "Hong Kong Tourists Association Quality
Taxi Drivers" at a ceremony here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The result of the award campaign is very encouraging and it
indicates that both local passengers and overseas tourists think
high of the taxi service quality in Hong Kong," said Jeffrey Lam,
chairman of the Quality Taxi Services Steering Committee of Hong
Kong, after presenting the prizes to award winners.
</P>
<P>
"The award may serve to recognize the endless efforts made by
the taxi drivers who provide professional service to passengers on
the one hand and contribute to a better image of Hong Kong on the
other," Lam said, adding "We shall continue our effort to
encourage taxi drivers to keep on their good work and help improve
the general service quality of the trade."
</P>
<P>
The nomination for the award took two months and taxi drivers
were assessed in accordance with criteria including reliability,
safety, customer service and overall passenger satisfactions, by a
working group consisting of transport officials, taxi trade
representatives and sponsors of the award.
</P>
<P>
The Outstanding Quality Taxi Drivers are the top ten drivers
who have obtained full marks from their nominators and they will
be presented "Outstanding Quality Taxi Driver" Certificate and
identity cards as well as some other prizes and oil coupons.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the Steering Committee, the Transport
Department and taxi associations, the award is one of the series
of projects launched to help improve the taxi service quality.
</P>
<P>
The award campaign was launched last January and passengers
were given a nomination form for them to nominate drivers
providing quality service. A total of 1,200 nominees were received
when the campaign closed on March 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
