<HEADLINE> HKSAR Signs Air Services Agreement with Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) signed an air services agreement
Wednesday with Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Ip, secretary for economic services of the HKSAR,
signed the agreement on behalf of the HKSAR government while
Mongolian Minister of Infrastructure Development G. Batkhuu signed
on behalf of the government of Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to closer links between Hong Kong and Mongolia.
I am encouraged by the fact that bilateral trade between Hong Kong
and Mongolia has increased by more than 80 percent in 1999, and
the number of Mongolian visitors coming to Hong Kong in the first
three months of this year has more than doubled," said Ip at the
signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"The Air Services Agreement provides a legal framework for the
establishment and future expansion of our bilateral air links. I
hope that with the conclusion of the agreement, there will soon be
direct air services between Hong Kong and Mongolia," he said.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR/Mongolia Air Services Agreement is the 43rd air
services agreement signed by the HKSAR government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
