<HEADLINE> Intel, Cable &AMP; Wireless HKT to Boost E-Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Intel Corporation and Cable &AMP;
Wireless HKT announced here Wednesday a memorandum of
understanding they had reached on accelerating e-business in Hong
Kong and the rest of the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Under the document, Intel will offer Intel Architecture-based
server platforms and Intel NetStructure communication products for
Powerbase, a newly branded data center services of Cable &AMP;
Wireless HKT.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also collaborate on e-home initiatives to
drive broadband Internet deployment in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Small- to medium-sized businesses are driving the Internet
economy growth in Hong Kong and Asia Pacific. Cable &AMP; Wireless HKT
understands how these businesses can participate in the digital
economy without high costs or technology barriers," said Intel
President and CEO Craig Barrett.
</P>
<P>
"Our agreement lets companies focus on their Internet business
by giving them a simple and reliable technology solution which
combines data outsourcing and web applications," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cable &AMP; Wireless HKT Chief Executive Linus Cheung said the
memorandum is a milestone in cooperation between the two
businesses and the partnership is poised to further boost Internet
development in the region. 
</P>
