<HEADLINE> Arafat Welcomes Israeli Pullout From South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
expressed here Wednesday his welcome of the just-completed Israeli
withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement, Arafat said "We have been stressing since
the very beginning that Israel has to implement U.N. Resolution 425
which is related to our people and land in Lebanon, which is proud
today to have every inch of its territories liberated."
</P>
<P>
Arafat voiced hope that the Israeli pullout from south Lebanon
would push forward the Mideast peace process and enhance Israel's
withdrawal from the Palestinian territories as well.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's advisor Nabil Abu Rdeineh said: "The Israeli pullout
from south Lebanon marks a necessary step that should be followed
with more steps in order to reach a comprehensive peace in the
Middle East."
</P>
<P>
The United Nations resolutions demanding Israel's pullout from
all occupied Arab territories must be implemented, he noted, adding
that this is the essence of real peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Minister of Parliament Affairs Nabil Amr described
the Israeli withdrawal from south lebanon as a great victory for
the Lebanese people.
</P>
<P>
"People are more powerful in their determination and endurance
than the armies," he said.
</P>
<P>
Israel concluded its hasty full-scale withdrawal from south
lebanon early Wednesday, ending 22 years of occupation of the
Lebanese territory. 
</P>
