<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McAllister Anfield-Bound  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Liverpool have signed Coventry
skipper Gary McAllister on a one-year deal, according to local
reports on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old midfielder is believed to have had talks with
Reds boss Gerard Houllier at Anfield this week. His contract with
the Sky Blues runs out on June 30, and McAllister will be
available for free under the Bosman ruling.
</P>
<P>
The Coventry veteran was top scorer at the midlands club with
13 goals last season and was voted Player of the Year.
</P>
<P>
Highfield Road chairman Bryan Richardson, however, denied any
knowledge of McAllister agreeing a move to Merseyside.
</P>
<P>
He said: "I've absolutely no knowledge whatsoever that that
decision has been made by him. I think there's no doubt at all
that the first people that will be informed will be Gordon
Strachan and myself," he told Coventry's official web site.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool press officer Ian Cotton remained tight-lipped over
the reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
