<HEADLINE> China to Provide 74 Mln Dollar Credit to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China National Electric Wire and
Cable Import/Export Corporation Wednesday agreed to provide a
supplier's credit amounting to 74 million U.S. dollars to the
government of Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
In this connection a loan agreement has been signed here
Wednesday between the Chinese corporation and the Economic
Relations Division (ERD) under the Bangladeshi Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Song Yueming, President of China National Electric Wire and
Cable Import/Export Corporation and Masihur Rahman, Secretary of
ERD, signed the agreement on behalf of their respective side.
Chinese Ambassador to Dhaka Wang Chungui also attended the signing
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be utilized for the implementation of
Rehabilitation, Renovation and Augmentation of 29 Nos. 132 KV Grid
Substations and 819 kilometers 132 KV Transmission Lines Project
under Bangladesh Power Development Board.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of this project, which will be constructed
at a cost of 108 million dollars, are to enhance the capacity of
existing 15 grid substations and renovation of 14 more substations
in the country, and to renovate existing 819 kilometers 132 KV
transmission line to increase transmission capacity reduction of
system loss. The project will be completed in 2002. 
</P>
