<HEADLINE> Target Set for Hi-Tech Program in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Science and
Technology published here today a list of 1,047 projects for this
year's Torch Program, a national program for developing the
country's hi-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The projects, which involve 103 major hi-tech enterprises,
include 58 key projects, including high-definition television,
large container inspection systems, and medicine for the treatment
of drug addiction.
</P>
<P>
The Torch Program Center, under the ministry, is applying for
bank loans of 6.5 billion yuan to finance these projects.
</P>
<P>
Many of the projects are related to electronics, computer and
Internet technology, and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The Torch Program began in 1988, and by the end of 1999 China
had launched more than 18,000 Torch Program projects, according to
official statistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
