<DOCNO> XIE20000524.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Union Leader Calls for Factory Democracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, president of the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions, has urged the serious study
of Jiang Zemin's important instructions on the Party's role, and
the promotion of democracy in factories.
</P>
<P>
Wei, a member of the Standing Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee Political Bureau, made the call
during his tour of Hebei Province on May 21-24.
</P>
<P>
Wei was in the province to inspect the "opening-up of factory
affairs," that is, the participation of factory workers in
democratic decision-making, management, and enterprise supervision.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang's instruction made during his south China
tour earlier this year, the working class is the political base of
the Party, and the Party must always maintain its nature as the
pioneer of the working class and adhere to the principal guideline
of depending on the working class wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
"Opening-up of factory affairs" should be practiced with a
focus on the general situation of enterprise reform, development,
and stability, Wei said, noting that the key is whether the
workers' democratic supervisory rights are ensured.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Wei visited a dozen local factories and held
talks with employee representatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
