<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tension in Indonesia's Aceh to Quiet Down, Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Minister of Defense
Juwono Sudarsono Wednesday said he is optimistic that tension and
armed conflict in Aceh province will soon quiet down.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that slowly but surely, tension and conflict in Aceh
will be quieting down within next one or two months," Sudarsono
told reporters here, citing that most of Aceh people want peace.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government representatives and the Free Aceh
Movement (GAM) -- an underground armed movement in Aceh province --
signed a Joint Understanding on Humanitarian Pause in Davos,
Switzerland, in mid-May under which both sides agreed to reduce
tension and violent actions in the territory.
</P>
<P>
But the three-month accord is not due to come into force until
June 2.
</P>
<P>
Since the signing of the accord, at least 15 people were killed
in clashes in the western-most province of Aceh. The Indonesian
Observer newspaper said the renewed violence raised fears that the
accord could be derailed.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, President Abdurrahman Wahid said that there are "
certain parties" attempting to disrupt the government peace
efforts in Aceh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
