<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading Egyptian newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Al Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak received Tuesday visiting
Israeli Public Security Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami and his
accompanying delegation.
</P>
<P>
Ben-Ami, who took part in the recently suspended talks with the
Palestinians in Stockholm, arrived in Cairo Monday to brief Mubarak
on the latest developments of the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- President Mubarak will chair on Wednesday two successive
meetings for the Ministerial Economic Group and the cabinet to
discuss a host of issues, including the economic situation and the
official measures taken so far to activate the market.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- The second Euro-Mediterranean Parliamentary Conference opened
Tuesday in Egypt's Mediterranean city of Alexandria and would
discuss peace and security in the area and ways of combating
terrorism and organized crime.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Egypt and Morocco signed Tuesday six agreements to boost
bilateral trade during the second visit of Moroccan King Mohammed
VI to Egypt since he took the throne last year.
</P>
<P>
President Mubarak and King Mohammed witnessed the signing
ceremony of the agreements on free trade, housing and development,
environment and the quality of industrial products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
