<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Establishes Special Scholarship Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 2,700 poor college students in
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region today were awarded
with "Spring Rain" scholarships for their studiousness and high
moral standards
</P>
<P>
This special scholarship program for poor college students was
initiated by the autonomous regional government last year with a
fund of two million yuan annually.
</P>
<P>
The winners, who received from 600 to 1,000 yuan in
scholarships for this year, account for 15 percent of all the poor
college students in Guangxi, according to a local education
official.
</P>
<P>
These students come from families with monthly incomes of less
than 120 yuan. Statistics show that there are a total of 81,000
students studying in colleges and universities in Guangxi, and the
poorer students account for 22.4 percent of the region's total
college student population.
</P>
<P>
To enable these students in Guangxi to continue their studies,
the regional government has also earmarked more than 10 million
yuan to provide them with part-time jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
