<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Receives More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan received 499.6 million U.
S. dollars of foreign investment (both direct and portfolio) in
the first 10 months (July 1999-April 2000) of the current fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
The 10-month figure is 11 percent higher than full last year at
403.3 million dollars, according to the latest figures released by
the National Bank of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The inflow of private foreign direct investment in the 10
months amounted to 392.5 million dollars, marking a 5 percent
increase of that of the same period of the previous year which
stood at 372 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The inflow of foreign portfolio investment during the 10 months
amounted to 5 million dollars, over 100 percent higher than full
last year at 27 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the total foreign investment, 172 million dollars was from
the United Kingdom, 110 million from the United States, 23.5
million dollars from the United Arab Emirates, 16 million from
Saudi Arabia and 16 million from Japan.
</P>
<P>
The mainstay of foreign direct investment are the power sector
which fetched about 61 million dollars, mining and oil exploration
with 60 million dollars, and chemical, pharmaceuticals and
fertilizer with 111 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
