<HEADLINE> 24 Abu Sayyaf Rebels Captured in Basilan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The extremist Abu Sayyaf Group has
been further decimated with the capture of 24 terrorists by the
military in southern Philippine island of Basilan during the past
few days, a military report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jaime Canatoy, chief of the army Public Affairs Service (PAS),
said it was the biggest haul by government troops against the Abu
Sayyaf since April 22 wen they fled their mountain lair in Sumisip
Complex.
</P>
<P>
Military statistics show that more than 70 Abu Sayyaf rebels
have been neutralized since the military launched an all-out war
against the terrorist group last month.
</P>
<P>
Before the attack on Mt. Mohadji, the military estimated there
were 250 Abu Sayyaf terrorists under the leadership of Khaddafy
Janjalani.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, 12 Abu Sayyaf members were captured during a
mopping-up operation by government forces. Seized from them were
seven high-powered firearms and over a thousand rounds of
ammunition.
</P>
<P>
Canatoy said 10 Abu Sayyaf terrorists were earlier captured on
May 20 and two others last week.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 members of the extremist group were killed when
government troops attacked Mt. Mohadji last month to rescue 29
civilians they took hostage on March 20.
</P>
<P>
Four of the hostages, including a priest, were executed by the
Abu Sayyaf when the soldiers were closing in.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen others were rescued and two others escaped, but the Abu
Sayyaf kidnapped a son of a slain soldier during an encounter in
Isabela last week.
</P>
<P>
As of Wednesday, the terrorist group is holding eight hostages.
</P>
<P>
According to Canatoy, the 24 captured Abu Sayyaf members will
be charged with kidnapping-for-ransom and murder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
