<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Continues to Weaken </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian currency continued
its weakening trend on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah traded at 8,495 (buying) and 8,515 (selling) per U.S.
dollar on Wednesday morning session, compared with 8,420 and 8,450
per dollar on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Managing Director of the PT. Central Intervest Corporation
Handoyo said the weakening of the rupiah was caused by the strong
demand for dollar in local market and other places such as Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the rupiah plunged into a six-month low level of 8,
500 per dollar.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Coordinating Minister for Economy, Finance and
Industry Kwik Kian Gie said the government wants the rupiah to
strengthen back to 7,000 against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Senior Deputy Governor of the Bank Indonesia (the
central bank) said the rupiah will continue to weaken if political
conflicts and lawlessness continued in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
