<HEADLINE> Estrada Calls on Filipinos to Unite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada,
who is on a visit to the central part of the country, called on
Filipinos to stop fighting and unite to fight poverty together, a
report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
"We should prove to the world that we can improve this country
together," Estrada was quoted as saying in his speech before
people of Guimaras province in the Visayas Wednesday noon.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency (PNA) said the president also
appealed to the people to help him fight poverty.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival in Guimaras, the PNA noted, Estrada started to
distribute checks to energize all communities of the province, for
the flood control project, roads and bridges projects of the
province.
</P>
<P>
He also distributed certified palay seeds, hybrid coconuts,
capital for duck raisers and vegetable garden farmers of Guimaras.
</P>
<P>
The president arrived in Guimaras Wednesday morning from
Bacolod city with some members of his Cabinet to inaugurate some
projects.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to be back in Bacolod City prior to his trip to
Metro Manila in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
