<HEADLINE> Task Force Set up in Zambia to Verify HIV/AIDS Cures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba
has constituted a task force of medical experts and government
officials to verify claims by some traditional healers that they
have found HIV/AIDS cures.
</P>
<P>
The group has also been tasked with the responsibility of
testing HIV patients, according to Zambia Daily Mail.
</P>
<P>
The patients will be selected by the traditional doctors and
tested by the experts of the task force.
</P>
<P>
Some patients found HIV positive are treated by the traditional
doctors claiming they have found the cures.
</P>
<P>
The task force has been sub-divided into three committees to
monitor the operations of the traditional healers and invalidate
or validate the claims about the cures for AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the University of Zambia Dean at the school of
medicine, professor Lupando Munkonge, as saying on Tuesday that
currently 30 patients are undergoing medication by the traditional
doctors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
