<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Fund COMESA Small, Medium Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has agreed
to assist in establishing a fund for Small and Medium Enterprises
(SMEs) in the Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa
(COMESA) region, Zambia Daily Mail reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This responded a proposal that COMESA assistant secretary
general Sindiso Ngwenya put forward early this month that it was
working on the establishment of the fund for SMEs.
</P>
<P>
Jochen Krebs, head of the EU delegation to Zambia, said in an
interview with the newspaper that creating centers for industrial
development in COMESA would significantly promote industrial
growth in the region that would launch a Free Trade Area (FTA) at
the end of October this year.
</P>
<P>
Ngwenya said that Zambia and Egypt would host the initial two
centers that would work towards the promotion of the SMEs.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the onset of the FTA may create some
problems for a number of SMEs, and the fund and development
centers will be expected to provide cushion to the growing
businesses.
</P>
<P>
The COMESA centers in Egypt and Zambia are expected to take off
in the next six months, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
