<HEADLINE> Russia Reiterates One-China Policy After New Taiwan Leader Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Russia has not changed and will not
change its stand on the Taiwan issue after the new leadership of
China's Taiwan province came into office on May 20, said the
Russian Foreign Ministry on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Moscow proceeds from the fact that there is only one China in
the world, while the government of the People's Republic of China
is its only legitimate government, the ministry stressed in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
It notes that Moscow does not maintain any interstate relations
with Taiwan and develops with it mutually advantageous trade,
economic, scientific, cultural and sport ties on a strictly
informal basis.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Federation regards relations between the PRC and
Taiwan as China's internal affair, the ministry stated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
