<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslavia Tuesday strongly condemned the U.S.-led
West for blocking it from attending the Dayton meeting, which is
being held in Brussels on Tuesday and Wednesday to review the
Dayton peace accord's implementation.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav government said the West's act to bar Yugoslavia's
participation in the gathering of foreign ministers from the
countries that signed the 1995 peace accord has violated the
Dayton treaty and undermined peace and stability in the region,
the Yugoslav state news agency Tanjug reported. (Yugoslavia-West-
Dayton Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- Hungary and Croatia announced Tuesday that they
will build and develop a strategic partnership between them.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Croatian Prime Minister Ivica Racan and his
counterpart, Orban Viktor, said at a joint news conference held
after their meeting that proceeding from their existing good
neighborhood, the two nations will take further measures to boost
their bilateral ties in all fields. (Hungary-Croats-Partnership)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel has completed its troop withdrawal from
south Lebanon, ending its 22-year occupation there well ahead of
schedule, military sources said Wednesday morning. (Israel-
Lebanon-Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. House of Representatives began debate
Tuesday on a landmark legislation to grant China permanent normal
trade relations (PNTR) status, one day before its vote on the bill.
</P>
<P>
Supporters say the passage of the bill would spur reform in
China and benefit U.S. companies eager to enter the vast Chinese
market while opponents argued that it would harm employment in the
United States. (US-China-PNTR Debate) 
</P>
</TEXT>
