<DOCNO> XIE20000524.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 90 Percent Of Obese Children Suffer from Fatty Liver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A survey has shown that as high as
90 percent of obese children in this north China's port city
suffer from fatty liver disease.
</P>
<P>
The survey on the relationship between blood pressure, blood
fat and fatty liver was carried out by the Tianjin Aimin Weight
Reduction Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The survey on 1,200-plus obese children revealed that the blood
fat level in these children is much higher than other children of
the same age. Thirty-five percent of the rather fat children
suffer from high blood pressure.
</P>
<P>
In China, incidence of animal fat stored in the fatty tissue of
the body among Chinese children is on rise. Experts said most
parents think that the more their children eat the better. However,
they do not realize what harm this is doing on their children,
experts said.
</P>
<P>
Experts concluded that the children's liver cells become fatty
because they absorb too much nutrition.
</P>
<P>
Experts also warned that high blood pressure and blood fat are
dangerous signals of fatty liver among obese children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000524.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
