<HEADLINE> U.S. PPG Expands China Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Pittsburgh Plate Glass
Corporation (PPG), a U.S. based plate glass and coating producer,
will spend seven million U.S. dollars to upgrade its four white
carbon black plants in China.
</P>
<P>
A PPG source said the move is designed to meet the increasing
demand for white carbon black in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The upgrade includes 1.3 million U.S. dollars to be used on a
new production line in PPG's Nanchang plant, a major white carbon
black producer in Nanchang, capital of east China's Jiangxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The plan went into operation seven years ago and has since
produced 120,000 tons of white carbon black.
</P>
<P>
With annual sales of 7.8 billion U.S. dollars, PPG has invested
a total of 60 million U.S. dollars in China in the past several
years.  
