<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops Vaccine against Pork Tapeworm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pigs receiving one or two injections of the vaccine are
immunized from the disease.
</P>
<P>
Both humans and pigs are susceptible to pork tapeworm infection,
and the disease has been widely spread in Asia, Africa, and Latin
America.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that about six million Chinese are suffering
from the disease. The pork tapeworm is found in about 10 million
pigs each year in China, with an infection rate of 30 percent,
causing over 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) in economic
losses annually.
</P>
<P>
The research program on the vaccine against the pork tapeworm
was listed as a key scientific research project during the Ninth
Five-Year-Plan period (1996-2000). 
</P>
</TEXT>
