<HEADLINE> Waste Water Pollutes Huangpu River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Waste water from households has
become the major source of pollution for the Huangpu River in
Shanghai, China's largest city.
</P>
<P>
According to a report on Shanghai's environment, the city's
total industrial waste water in 1999 amounted to 850 million tons
while household waste water was 1.17 billion tons.
</P>
<P>
The insufficient disposal of household waste water in suburban
towns is another cause of pollution.
</P>
<P>
Sheng Yonglin, an expert from the Shanghai Environment
Protection Bureau, said that speeding up the construction of waste
water disposal facilities is key to curbing the situation.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal government plans to raise the waste water
disposal rate to more than 95 per cent by 2020, compared with the
current 15 percent. 
</P>
