<HEADLINE> Bird Discovered on Tibetan Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A group of 16 islands with a variety
of birds have recently been found at Yamzho Lake in southwest
China's Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Yamzho Lake, the largest inland lake in southern Tibet, has a
water surface of 638 square kilometers with an elevation of 4,400
meters. The lake is dotted with 16 islands of different sizes.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of birds migrated to Seduo Island recently. They
include brown-head gulls, black-neck cranes and Tibetan snow
roosters. "The island has 2,800 bird nests," said a local bird
watcher.  
</P>
