<HEADLINE> Top Think Tank to Help Westward Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS), the state's top think tank, plans to organize two
groups of experts to visit Sichuan an Guizhou provinces and
Chongqing Municipality in order to undertake an on-the-spot
investigations.
</P>
<P>
After the two-week study tour which will begin tomorrow, the
experts, all members of the academic committee of the CASS, are
expected to propose plans to boost economic development of these
southwestern parts of China, a CASS official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The experts will carry out surveys of economic and social
conditions in these areas, and some will hold seminars on a number
of hot issues in China.
</P>
<P>
The central authorities have put forward a major plan for the
massive development of western China.  
