<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Completes Withdrawal from South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli troops poured out of south
Lebanon into Israel under the cover of darkness on Wednesday,
ending 22 years of occupation of south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Prime Minister Ehud Barak, who is also defense
minister, ordered in small hours of Wednesday all the Israeli
troops to quit south Lebanon. He also appealed to all sides to show
restraint.
</P>
<P>
"In accordance with the decision of the security cabinet on
Monday, May 22, 2000, which empowers the prime minister and defense
minister, in consultation with the chief of general staff, to
decide on the date of the withdrawal from Lebanon, the prime
minister and defense minister ordered the withdrawal of the Israel
Defense Forces from Lebanon," Barak's order said.
</P>
<P>
While issuing the order, Barak also calls on the power factors
in Lebanon to exercise restraint and responsibility, and says that
Israel will react severely to any attack on its sovereignty, its
civilians and its soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the Israeli-Lebanese border said during the
withdrawal, tanks and armoured personnel carriers loaded with
soldiers entered Israel through various border crossings. The
armoured cars kicked up dust as they rumbled across the border.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military said all of the outposts belonging to the
Israeli army and its South Lebanon Army (SLA) allies in the
security zone had been abandoned and most were blown up.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the pullout operations, the sound of heavy shelling
could be heard, the sky dyed red by flares Israeli aircraft
launched to light the way out. But no one was hurt, the military
said.
</P>
<P>
Barak has sent a letter to the United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan, accusing Syria of doing all it could to sabotage the
withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
"To this end, it has been preparing the ground for violent acts
against Israel" after its withdrawal was completed, Barak said in
the letter, urging the United Nations to send peacekeeping forces
into south Lebanon as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
While the withdrawal was going on, thousands of SLA and their
family members sought refugee in Israel and nearly 4,000 of them
have already entered Israel during the last 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
Official announcement of the completion of withdrawal is
expected soon.
</P>
<P>
Israel deployed in south Lebanon from 1978 with the self-
declared purpose of halting cross-border attacks and set up the
security zone in 1985 for the same purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
