<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Microsoft Corp. President Bill Gates wrote in
Tuesday's Washington Post, calling U.S. Congress to grant China
permanent normal trade relations (PNTR) status.
</P>
<P>
In an article titled "Yes, More Trade With China," Gates said
he could not agree more with Federal Reserve Chairman Alan
Greenspan's recent comment that the outcome of the PNTR vote will
have profound implications for the free trading system and the
long-term growth potential of the U.S. economy. (Microsoft-Bill
Gates-PNTR)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Thai cabinet has approved a plan to mobilize a
total fund of 42 billion baht (1.1 billion US dollars) to help
small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), Thai Ministry of
Industry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The fund, plus another 4.0 billion baht (100 million US dollars)
as guarantee money, will be raised by six government banks and
financial institutions, according to a report from the Ministry of
Industry. (Thailand-Loan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain's housing market has reached a peak and will
fall sharply next year, a leading group of forecasters has warned.
</P>
<P>
Across Britain, price rises will be 12 percent this year before
falling back to 5 percent in the following year, according to a
new report by Cambridge Econometrics. ( UK-House Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- China and India will outpace Japan in Internet
growth in the near future, according to predictions made by a U.S.
research firm providing statistics and demographic data about
Internet users.
</P>
<P>
China's active Internet user base will grow from 2.5 million in
1999 to 21 million by 2003, an increase of 750 percent, said
eMarketer in its eAsia report. India's active Internet use will
reach 9 million in 2003, from just 270,000 in 1999. (Japan-
Internet Dominance)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Indonesian government has designed a new farming
concept to help boost efficiency in the agricultural sector,
according to Minister of Agriculture M. Prakosa.
</P>
<P>
Under the corporate farming concept, small farm areas of
between 0.3 and 0.4 hectare would be consolidated into a corporate
farming unit with a land size of between 100 hectares and 150
hectares for efficiency. (Indonesia-New Farming Concept)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canada's benchmark Toronto Stock Exchange (TSE) 300
Index closed down 306.56 points Tuesday to 8,986.60, the biggest
single-day drop for the month.
</P>
<P>
It was also the first time for TSE to be dragged down below 9,
000 this month after the main stock index recovered from its
record losing week in mid-April, when the stocks tumbled more than
1,000 points below 9,000 from eye-popping highs of up to 10,000. (
Toronto-Stocks) 
</P>
