<HEADLINE> Men's Beach Volleyball World Tour Held in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Beach Volleyball Men's Open,
one leg of the Beach Volleyball World Tour 2000 of the
International Volleyball Federation (FIVB), was launched here
Wednesday with the participation of 55 teams from 26 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
Qualification tournament will be held Wednesday and Thursday by
way of double elimination. The teams are placed in the bracket
according to their points in the FIVB World ranking. After one
loss the team moves to the losers bracket and competes until it
loses a second match, when it is eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The winning teams will have the main draw on May 26 and 27. And
semi-final and final matches are to be held on May 28.
</P>
<P>
The champion team will obtain a prize money of 26,000 U.S.
dollars and the second-place team will get 18,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Three teams from the inland areas of China take part in the
beach volleyball competition.
</P>
<P>
In view of Macao's outstanding organizing ability of the Women
World Grand Prix for six years, FIVB has given Macao the right to
host the men's beach volleyball this year and the year 2001.
</P>
</TEXT>
