<HEADLINE> Thai Gov't to Fund Small, Medium-sized Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet has approved a
plan to mobilize a total fund of 42 billion baht (1.1 billion US
dollars) to help small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), Thai
Ministry of Industry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The fund, plus another 4.0 billion baht (100 million US dollars)
as guarantee money, will be raised by six government banks and
financial institutions, according to a report from the Ministry of
Industry.
</P>
<P>
The loan interest rates charged by these institutions will vary
according to the nature of each institution, it said.
</P>
<P>
