institutions will give priority to the SMEs engaged in
manufacturing products for exports, employment opportunities,
rural-based industries, and energy development.
</P>
<P>
The SMEs will have plenty of time to apply for the funds, one
year starting from now, it added.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the government banks and financial institutions
provided a total of 35.5 billion baht (0.92 billion US dollars) to
the SMEs in combined loans, it said. 
