<HEADLINE> Hungary, Croatia to Build Strategic Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Hungary and Croatia announced
Tuesday that they will build and develop a strategic partnership
between them.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Croatian Prime Minister Ivica Racan and his
counterpart, Orban Viktor, said at a joint news conference held
after their meeting that proceeding from their existing good
neighborhood, the two nations will take further measures to boost
their bilateral ties in all fields.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to revamp and enlarge Croatia's port Rijeka on the
Adriatic through combined investment and joint ventures, that they
will improve the railroad transportation between Budapest and
Rijeka, and build a high-grade highway linking Budapest and Zagreb.
</P>
<P>
The prime ministers added that they will also step up
negotiations on a free trade agreement.
</P>
<P>
Viktor said that two years ago Hungary started carrying out a
new Central Europe policy, which includes establishing strategic
partnership with Croatia. He hoped Croatia could join the
cooperation among Hungary, Italy and Slovenia as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Racan and Viktor also signed on Tuesday an accord on mutual
exemption of visas, which will allow, as from June, citizens of
the two countries to travel across the border with their identity
cards only.
</P>
<P>
Racan, who is on his first trip to Hungary after becoming prime
minister in January, arrived here on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
