Area, an emerging financial and trade zone set up in the early
1990s, topped 4.08 billion US dollars in the first four months of
the year, an increase of 113.9 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
More than 67 percent of imports were done by overseas-funded
enterprises in the area, including Shanghai General Motors, a Sino-
US joint venture, which imported 147 million US dollars of
automobile parts, a year-on-year surge of 781.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
About 846 million US dollars of imports came from Japan from
January to April, an increase of 127.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the area garnered a total of 2.34 billion US dollars
from exports, up 33.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Major export commodities included machinery and electrical
equipment, clothing, and electronic products.  
