<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toronto Stocks Down Below 9,000 Points Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Canada's benchmark Toronto Stock
Exchange (TSE) 300 Index closed down 306.56 points Tuesday to 8,
986.60, the biggest single-day drop for the month.
</P>
<P>
It was also the first time for TSE to be dragged down below 9,
000 this month after the main stock index recovered from its
record losing week in mid-April, when the stocks tumbled more than
1,000 points below 9,000 from eye-popping highs of up to 10,000.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's plunge resulted from concerns about uncertainties of
technology stocks and, particularly, interest rates, which were
feared to be raised again to affect the economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The index, however, is still up 573 points for this year.
</P>
<P>
Leading the way down was 724 Solutions Inc. (SVN-T), which lost
12.70 Canadian dollars (about 8.49 U.S. dollars) to sit at 50
dollars (about 33.42 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Another falling tech heavyweight is Nortel Networks Corp. (NT-T)
, which was off 5.90 dollars (about 3.94 U.S. dollars) at 72.95 (
about 48.75 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the overall market, losers beat advancers 784 to 357 with
237 issues flat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
