<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold Mid-Year Gems Emporium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will hold this year's mid-
year gems emporium, which is the ninth of its kind, in October to
put on sale locally-produced gems, pearl and jewelry through
competitive bidding or tender, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mid-year gems emporiums were introduced since 1992 in addition
to annual events which have been held since 1964.
</P>
<P>
At the 37th annual Myanma Gems Emporium, held in March this
year, a total of 23.847 million U.S. dollars were fetched,
breaking the past highest record of 1990's 27th Myanma gems
emporium which earned 14.839 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The 37th annual gems emporium attracted 437 foreign gems
merchants of 215 companies from 11 countries and regions as well
as 183 local gems traders.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is a well-known producer of jade, ruby and sapphire in
the world and the country earned a total of over 300 million
dollars from its 37 annual and eight mid-year gems emporiums,
according to official statistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
