<HEADLINE> More Drug Unearthed in Tajik Embassy in Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh police have seized more
cocaine in an international drug smuggling scandal which involved
the Tajik embassy in Kazakhstan, reports said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, 24 kilograms of cocaine were discovered in a house
and a garage belonging to Tajikistan's trade representative in
Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The discovery followed a Kazakh announcement Monday that two
cars of the Tajik embassy had been used in smuggling narcotics
from Tajikistan to Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The two cars detained by Kazakh security officials in Alma-Ata
contained 62 kilograms of cocaine. Also seized was a great amount
of cash and checks.
</P>
<P>
Five Tajik nationals have so far been arrested, police said.
</P>
<P>
Tajik Ambassador Saduladzhan Negmatov said he felt surprised
and sad that embassy officials had been involved in drug
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine could be destined both for dealers in Alma-Ata and
in Russia and Western Europe, according to police. 
</P>
