<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Heritage Site to Host International Art Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The county of Dazu in southwest
China's Chongqing Municipality will host an international art
festival from June 5 to 10.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day event, business, trade and tourism promotion
activities and cultural exchanges will also be held. Meanwhile,
the county will open a group of new scenic spots and three new
tourism routes.
</P>
<P>
Preferential policies will be worked out to encourage domestic
and overseas investment in the tourist sector, according to a
local senior official.
</P>
<P>
Dazu, well known for more than 50,000 stone sculptures in
northwestern Chongqing, was put on the World Heritage List in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the sculptures were carved during the late Tang
Dynasty (618-907) and the Song Dynasty (960-1279). And the Dazu
sculptures marked the second consummate level of carving arts in
Chinese history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
