ANKARA -- The Turkish military on Tuesday dismissed the widely-
spread speculation that Turkey may take the initiative to
dismantle its Aegean Army as a "goodwill gesture" to Greece.
</P>
<P>
"In recent days, certain press organizations have been
publishing news and comments to the effect that the General Staff
views the dismantling of the Aegean Army as a positive step," said
a statement, adding that "Chief of General Staff General Huseyin
Kivrikoglu has not exchanged views with anybody over abolishing
the Aegean Army." (Turkey-Army)
</P>
