UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan Tuesday
called on Morocco and the Polisario Front to come up with specific
solutions to problems that have delayed a referendum on the future
of Western Sahara for more than eight years.
</P>
<P>
Annan, in his written report to the U.N. Security Council,
said face-to-face talks held on May 14 in London under the
auspices of his special envoy, former U.S. Secretary of State
James Baker, only reinforced the U.N. assessment of "their widely
divergent positions." (UN-Morocco)
</P>
<P>
