</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. federal investigators Tuesday predicted a
difficult task in determining the cause of a recent plane crash
that killed 19 people without "black box" date to analyze.
</P>
<P>
The charter airplane's cockpit voice recorder is blank, said
George Black, a National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB)
investigator. (US-Plane Crash)
</P>
<P>
