<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Confiscates 28 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- A Bulgarian customs office seized 28.
4 kilograms of heroin at the Bulgarian-Turkish border checkpoint
of Kapitan Andreevo Tuesday morning, local Svilengrad customs
officer Kalina Petrova said.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers found 54 packages of heroin concealed between
the luggage compartment and engine of a Turkish-registered
Mercedes bus bound for Bucharest, capital of Romania, when they
stopped the bus for a thorough check.
</P>
<P>
A 48-year-old Turk suspected of drug trafficking was arrested.
The case has been handed over to the investigative authorities,
said Petrova.
</P>
<P>
Svilengrad customs offices confiscated a total of 634.6
kilograms of heroin since the beginning of this year. 
</P>
