<HEADLINE> Matthaeus not to Play for SpVgg Unterhaching </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Germany captain Lothar
Matthaeus denied to play for another Munich club, first division
SpVgg Unterhaching.
</P>
<P>
The former Bayern Munich star, in U.S. Major League Soccer for
the last two months, was quoted as saying that he refused a
potentially lucrative offer from club sponsor Erich Lejeune, chief
executive of CE Computer Electronic to work as a consultant for
his firm.
</P>
<P>
Unterhaching shocked Bundesliga leaders Bayer Leverkusen for a
2-0 home win on Saturday to help neighbouring giants Bayern snatch
a record 16th crown.
</P>
<P>
Matthaeus, 39 and holder of a record 146 caps, was named in
Germany's Euro 2000 squad on Monday. 
</P>
