<HEADLINE> Euro 2000 Police Intelligence Unit to Be Ready on June 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Belgian and Dutch police said on
Tuesday the unit to coordinate public order information during the
European soccer championships would be fully prepared on June 6.
</P>
<P>
The Bi-national Center for Police Intelligence (BIPC) will
collect, verify and analyse all police information, using 60
police officers from all participating countries. The BIPC will be
staffed on a round-the-clock basis.
</P>
<P>
Until then international police services will deal with Belgian
and Dutch police forces separately.
</P>
<P>
Euro 2000 is being co-hosted by Belgium and the Netherlands
from June 10 to July 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
