<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inter Milan Qualifies for European Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Roberto Baggio scored twice for Inter
Milan as his side defeated Parma 3-1 in Verona on Tuesday to
clinch a place in next season's European Champions League.
</P>
<P>
Baggio, widely expected to leave Inter after spending much of
this year on the bench, curled a free kick inside Gianluigi Buffon
's near post after 35 minutes to give Inter the lead in the end-of-
season play-off.
</P>
<P>
Parma levelled the score after 70 minutes through Croatian
midfielder and second half substitute Mario Stanic.
</P>
<P>
But 13 minutes later Baggio sealed Inter's win with a fine
strike from the edge of the area.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Ivan Zamorano added a third goal in the final minute.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan will join champions Lazio, Juventus and AC Milan in
the Champions League. Parma will contest the UEFA Cup for the
third year running alongside AS Roma and Fiorentina.
</P>
<P>
Inter and Parma finished the season level on points in fourth
and fifth place respectively.
</P>
<P>
Baggio's double strike will inevitably fuel speculation about
his future at Inter.
</P>
<P>
Baggio has played 24 times for Inter in all competitions this
term but has been used for the full 90 minutes only occasionally,
all in the past month.
</P>
<P>
Baggio's took his goals tally for the season to five and put
Inter back in Europe's premier competition after a one-year
absence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
