<HEADLINE> Tianjin to Hold Intl. Children's Culture and Art Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 24 (Xinhua) -- This north China port city will
host an international children's culture and art festival from
August 5 through 10.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government of Tianjin and the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) are
organizers of the festival. The theme of the event is peace,
friendship and the future.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,200 children worldwide will attend the festival, and
some 30 children's art troupes from a dozen countries and regions,
including China, the United States, Russia and Japan, will stage
various performances during the six-day event.
</P>
<P>
An international children's painting exhibition is also
scheduled.  
</P>
