<HEADLINE> China's Retail Exposition Scheduled For August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth China Retail Conference
and Exposition is scheduled for mid-August in Shanghai, China's
leading industrial and commercial city.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, co-sponsored by the China Federation of
Commerce and the Shanghai Council of Commerce, will draw 500
manufacturers and traders from more than 30 countries, including
the United States, the Netherlands, Japan, Singapore, and the
Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The annual event is China's largest display of the world's most
advanced commercial equipment, software, foodstuffs and retail
technology.
</P>
<P>
A series of forums, workshops and lectures on modern retail
business, automatic commerce and supermarket management will be
held during the expo. 
</P>
