<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Jewelry Demand Remains Strong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The jewelry demand in China is
running strong as more Chinese have the cash to buy what used to
be considered a luxury.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the administration center of jewelry under the
Ministry of Land and Resources show that in 1999, 80 billion yuan-
worth (9.6 billion U.S. dollars) of jewelry was sold on the
domestic market, and 2.14 billion U.S. dollars-worth of jewelry
was exported.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Peili, vice-president of the China Jewelry Association,
said jewelry manufacturing and selling in China have reached a
considerable scale, and the use of high-tech and advanced
craftsmanship and technique have become a common feature of the
industry.
</P>
<P>
Some 24,500 enterprises, either state-owned or private, are now
involved in the jewelry-making business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
