<HEADLINE> Cole Given Three Days to Prove Fitness  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Andy Cole could miss out on England'
s Euro 2000 bid due to a nagging toe injury.
</P>
<P>
The Manchester United striker has been given three days to
prove his fitness by England coach Kevin Keegan.
</P>
<P>
Cole has already been ruled out of England's friendly with
Brazil on Saturday but is still hoping to get the nod when Keegan
names his 22 for Holland and Belgium on May 31.
</P>
<P>
The injury is another blow to Keegan, who has already lost
Jason Wilcox with a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
But Liverpool striker Michael Owen has declared himself fit at
the end of an injury-riddled domestic season.
</P>
<P>
England boss Keegan confirmed: "I have told Andy Cole not to
worry about getting fit for Brazil on Saturday, just to make sure
that when I name my 22 he is fit and ready."
</P>
<P>
"I've asked Andy to train flat out for three days and then go
for a verdict. I want him to be fit, contrary to what some people
think," added the England coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
