<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Whitewashes Wales in Soccer Friendly  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Brazil proved too strong for the
Welsh soccer team when the visitors scored three goals in a spell
of 10 minutes in the second half of a friendly match in Cardiff
Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The 3-0 win was Brazil's first in Cardiff. A draw on their
first visit in 1983 was followed by a 1-0 defeat in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Elber opened the floodgates in the 62nd minute after a young
Wales side had largely held their own against the beaten World Cup

finalists in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The Bayern Munich striker was left with a simple tap-in after
goalkeeper Roger Freestone had made fine saves with his feet from
Franca and Ze Roberto.
</P>
<P>
John Robinson came close to equalising two minutes later with a
raking, left-foot shot which came back off the inside of the post.
But from then on Brazil stepped up a gear and turned on the style.
</P>
<P>
Cafu made it 2-0 with a superb, dipping volley and World Player
of the Year Rivaldo, who had orchestrated much of the Brazilian
build-up, added the third in the 72nd minute with a fierce header
from Denilson's exquisite cross.
</P>
<P>
A largely uninspiring first half had come to life in the final
few minutes when first Wales and then Brazil came close to
breaking the deadlock from deadball situations.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeeper Dida was surprised by a fiercely struck Gary Speed
free kick. He spilled the the ball and it had to be hooked away to
safety.
</P>
<P>
Then Cesar Sampaio was left unmarked to power in a header from
Rivaldo's corner but his effort was well saved by Freestone.
</P>
<P>
Brazil complete their short tour with another friendly against
England at Wembley on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
