<HEADLINE> Quaranta Wins 10th Stage in Giro d'Italia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian Ivan Quaranta claimed his
second stage win in the Giro d'Italia cycling race on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
As Czech Jan Svorada and Italy's Mario Cipollini shaped up for
another scrap in the final meters of the 10th stage, Quaranta
stormed to win the 248 kilometers leg from San Marcello Pistoiese
to Padua.
</P>
