<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Reports Big Export Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 24 (Xinhua) --South China's Guangdong Province
exported 27.44 billion U.S. dollars worth of commodities in the
first four months of the year, up 38.5 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
From January to April, the province did 49.98 billion U.S.
dollars-worth of foreign trade, up 33.4 percent from last year and
accounting for 36.5 percent of the country's total foreign trade,
according to the provincial customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
Most of the province's exports in the past four months were
from state-owned businesses and overseas-funded companies.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electronic products, garments and fashion
accessories made up the majority of the exports.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, the United States and the European Union continue to
be Guangdong's major export destinations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
