<HEADLINE> Keegan Excited by England Team Quality  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- English football team manager Kevin
Keegan has admitted the excitement is beginning to build as he
begins his final preparations to lead England into Euro 2000.
</P>
<P>
The England coach conceded expectations were "realistically"
low after an unconvincing performance in qualifying for the
championships in Holland and Belgium.
</P>
<P>
But, speaking ahead of the forthcoming friendlies against
Brazil and the Ukraine, he insisted England do have the quality to
win Euro 2000 this summer.
</P>
<P>
"I feel very, very excited," Keegan said. "The downside of that
is you probably will get nervous towards the start of a
competition because you realise what is at stake."
</P>
<P>
"You know that the nation are behind you and they expect so,
you feel all those things. I think any manager who sits in front
of you, he may well pretend he does not but I think you need to
feel all those things. I think players need to feel tensions and
nervous before they go out," he said. 
</P>
