<HEADLINE> Treble Triumph Could Earn Man United More Silverware  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Treble winners Manchester United may
have to make room in their over-crowded trophy cabinet for yet
another piece of silverware when the inaugural Laureus Sports
Awards are presented on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
United have been shortlisted in the world team of the year
category in recognition of their historic Treble success in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Their two rivals for the accolade are Australia's World Cup-
winning rugby union side and the United States' women's football
team, who also won their World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Alex Ferguson, accompanied by Ryan Giggs and Ronny Johnsen,
will be present at the gala presentation evening at the Sporting
Club in Monte Carlo after attending Wednesday's Champions League
final in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Ferguson was thrilled by United's nomination and said: "We are
all very proud. It's a magnificent honour for the club to be
shortlisted for this award."
</P>
<P>
The other categories are world sportsman of the year, world
sportswoman of the year, world alternative sportsperson of the
year, world sportsperson of the year with a disability, world
comeback of the year and world newcomer of the year.
</P>
<P>
The nominees have been selected by journalists from all over
the world and the winners will be chosen by a newly-founded 36-
member world sports academy, which includes Bobby Charlton, Ian
Botham, Sebastian Coe and Daley Thompson.
</P>
<P>
The Laureus Sports Awards have been established by
DaimlerChrysler and Richemont as the sporting equivalent of the
Oscars and the ceremony promises to be a glittering event attended
by film stars, pop stars and models.
</P>
<P>
The evening will be hosted by Jeff Bridges, Ashley Judd and
Dylan McDermott, while Samuel L Jackson, Sylvester Stallone and
Goldie Hawn will present some of the awards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
