<HEADLINE> Israeli-Palestinian Talks to be Resumed Soon: PNA Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Minister of State with the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) Hassan Asfour hinted on Wednesday that the
final-status talks between Israel and the Palestinians will be
resumed soon.
</P>
<P>
Asfour, who had also taken part in the back-channel talks in
Stockholm, told reporters here that the Palestinian side is against
any division or postponement of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinians have been holding back-door talks in
the Swedish capital in a bid to forge a framework for a final peace
deal after decades of conflict.
</P>
<P>
The existence of the parallel channel was revealed on May 14,
the day just after the two sides missed the second deadline for the
framework deal.
</P>
<P>
The final-status talks, halted by Israel after recent shoot-outs
between the Palestinian police and Israeli soldiers in the West
Bank and Gaza Strip, deal with the most thorniest issues, including
the status of Jerusalem, borders, water sharing, the fate of the
Palestinian refugees and Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza Strip declared on May 19
and 20 as "Days of Rage," during which they staged large-scale
protests to press Israel to release the 1,650 Palestinian prisoners
held in Israeli jails on security charges.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian prisoners have been on a hunger strike since
early May in protest against inhumane treatment inside the Israeli
jails.
</P>
<P>
The protests turned into violent clashes between the
Palestinians and the Israeli army, killing nine Palestinians and
injuring more than 1,000 others. 
</P>
