<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The foreign reserves of the
Central Bank of Uruguay (CBU) increased by 29 million U.S. dollars
in April to reach a net reserve level of 2.55 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
This amount represents an increase during the first four months
of the year of 112 million U.S. dollars, according to local press
reports.
</P>
<P>
In the first third of the year, the reserves increase has
happened due to bank deposits in the CBU, amounting to 241 million
U.S. dollars, and in a different sense, due to foreign currency
sales amounting to 112 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
This figure differs from what had been previously forecasted in
the monetary program which established foreign currency reserve
earnings for the whole year. 
