<HEADLINE> 32 Injured in German Train Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, May 24 (Xinhua)-Thirty two people were injured
Wednesday when a regional passenger train on false track collided
with a goods train parked at the station of Hadamar near Frankfurt,
a police spokesman said in Giessen.
</P>
<P>
 Six people among them were sent to nearby hospital with"
serious injuries", said the spokesman, adding that more than 70
fire fighters and emergency doctors were deployed after the
accident.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 people, most of them students, were on board the
passenger train when it crashed with the goods train.
</P>
<P>
The police attributed the accident to a wrong-placed track
fork after preliminary investigation and called it "man-made." A
state prosecutor office will take over the investigation. 
</P>
