<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rebound Strongly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rebounded
strongly Wednesday as investors returned to the market for bargain-
hunting.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 113.08 at 10,535.35,
bouncing back from an early falling.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index also rose 106.06 at
3,270.61. The composite fell as much as 121 points earlier in the
session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 25.19 at 1,399.05.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rallied as investors moved in the market to seek
bargains after steep falling. The stock market has suffered a lot
from higher interest rates and the Nasdaq index in particular lost
15 percent in the past five sessions.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Federal Reserve raised interest rates for the
sixth time since last June in an effort to keep inflation under
control. Higher rates cut corporate earnings by raising borrowing
costs.
</P>
<P>
Despite worries about higher rates still in place, investors
bought stocks of big names at the bargain price. Cisco Systems,
Intel and Applied Materials rose.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 4.90 at 635.18 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 2.73 at 461.74. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 1.41 at 887.89.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,500 down, 1,426 up and 500
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.13 billion shares from 862.25
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
